Long ago, magic was as commonplace as the people who walk
our lands. Communing with nature and the the spirits,
people came together and formed a society that thrived
through the use of divine enchantment to better their lives.
From the youngest to the eldest, magic was embraced and
spirituality guided the hand of the people.
In time, new technologies began to arise. With the dawn of
a new empire and the advances of steam technology,
the people of the world were soon able to do much more with
physical sciences and the ethereal nature of incantations
became the "old way."
The Empire, now embracing new technologies, grew to see
magic as being a threat to their reign over the people and
sought to limit the influence of the divine.
Through a campaign of misinformation and violence, magic
was purged from the continent. Practitioners of the ancient
craft were mercilessly slaughtered. Now, the few survivors
of this campaign live in fear and exile,
far from the Empire.
The rise of technology has begun a new age where
the quality of life of most citizens has improved, but
a shadow is slowly spreading across the land and the veil
is about to be lifted.
